    <note>Li(2) Heng [7276] Father-in-law of Chen(1) Xiang(3)'s [7005] descendant, Chen(1) Zun [7131], who moved to Kunshan after the marriage to Heng's daughter. Heng had earlier moved from Yangzhou, Jiangdu xian to Suzhou, Kunshan xian. Heng's father, Yu(4) [3550], was Superintendent of horse procurement in Guangxi (Tiju Guangxi maima) in 1133-34. CBD has jinshi in 1132, which would make entrance age closer to the average, but the Suzhou FZ would seem to be most reliable and also follows the listing in the Yangzhou FZ cited in YLDD. XNYL, 70.8b, 78.12b; Suzhou FZ, 139.22a; YLDD, 2368.6a, 10422.7a-10a; Yufeng zhi, 'zhong,' 53a. Weiyang Z (1542), 22.2a-3b. CBD, 2, 917-8.</note>
